RACE.FOOTNOTES: ICY REPLY was bumped at the start then pushed into another rival, showed speed while forced in early then steadied when the pacesetter crossed in front outside the five-eighths, regained stride and established a good position just off the pace, drafted in the two path around the turn, was asked near the quarter-pole, rallied four wide into upper stretch, closed well under a brisk hand-ride to get the lead approaching the furlong marker, disposed of the runner-up under a continued brisk hand-ride into the final sixteenth, was given one pop of a right-handed crop about forty yards from the wire and proved much the best under good handling. GREATEST LOVE pressed the pace down the backstretch, vied in the three path around the turn, gained a short lead outside the quarter-pole, was asked for her best in upper stretch while put to the crop, lost the advantage to the winner nearing the furlong marker and proved no match while clear for the place. SCOTT ALAIA broke out then bobbled, moved out under coaxing, was roused for more late on the backstretch, traveled three wide around the turn, was driven six wide into upper stretch and narrowly earned the show. TRADE SECRET was hustled from the start, chased the pace on the outside then in the four path around the turn, was driven five wide into upper stretch, dropped back into the final furlong and weakened then just missed the show. BEAUTIFUL KAREN bumped soundly with a rival at the start, angled in fast while going to the front, reached the rail before the five-eighths, showed the way on the inside of foes, vied along the rail on the turn, lost the lead to the runner-up outside the quarter-pole, dropped back under a drive in upper stretch and tired. GIRL OF TOSCONOVA was urged along towards the rear, saved ground on the turn, moved off the rail late on that bend, drifted out in the final furlong and was no factor. KEEN DANCER broke out and bumped with a rival then dropped back in tight quarters, dropped well behind the rest of the field, rounded the turn in the two path, spun three wide into the stretch, remained on her inside lead to the furlong marker then swapped to the proper lead and never reached contention. GRINGOTTS was urged along on the far outside, went five wide around the turn, came seven wide into upper stretch and capitulated.
